instruction:
Write a function `addItems` that takes four parameters:
* `firstName` - the data type must be `string`,
* `lastName` - the data type must be `string`,
* `age` - the data type must be `number`,
* `isStudent` - the data type must be `boolean`.


The function must return a new object, in which the properties should be added if they match the data types,
specified above.
If any of the properties do not match the data type, they should not be added to the object.
If all properties do not match the data type, the function should return an empty object.


An example of running a function:
```javascript
addItems('John', 'Doe', 25, true); // { firstName: "John", lastName: "Doe", age: 25, isStudent: true }
addItems(undefined, undefined, null, null); // {}
addItems('Angel', 'Fisk', null, null); // { firstName: "Angel", lastName: "Fisk" }
```

Similar example:
```javascript
function addItems(name, year, isOnSale) {
const obj = {};
if (typeof name === 'string') obj.name = name;
if (typeof year === 'number') obj.year = year;
if (typeof isOnSale === 'boolean') obj.isOnSale = isOnSale;
return obj;
}
```
